===Background===
House Greyjoy is one of the [[Great Houses]] of [[Westeros]]. Their lands are the [[Iron Islands]] off the west coast of the continent. They rule from their castle [[Pyke (castle)|Pyke]] from the [[Pyke (island)|island of the same name]]. The Iron Islands are harsh and bleak and the Greyjoys have traditionally survived by raiding their neighbors. They have always had plans to conquer the mainland. The head of the house is the [[Lord Reaper of Pyke]].&lt;ref name=&quot;House Greyjoy viewers guide&quot;&gt;[http://viewers-guide.hbo.com/game-of-thrones/season2/#!/guide/houses/greyjoy/ HBO viewers guide, season 2 guide to houses, House Greyjoy entry]&lt;/ref&gt;

House Greyjoy boasts descent from the [[Grey King]], a legendary [[King of the Iron Islands]] said to have ruled for a thousand years and taken a mermaid as wife. Like the vast majority of [[ironborn]], they worship theÂ [[Drowned God]].&lt;ref name=&quot;House Greyjoy viewers guide&quot; /&gt;

Lord [[Balon Greyjoy]] is the most recent head of the house. He led [[Greyjoy Rebellion|a rebellion]] against King [[Robert Baratheon]] eight years before the events of the series begin. Balon's sons [[Rodrik Greyjoy|Rodrik]] and [[Maron Greyjoy|Maron]] were killed in the unsuccessful rebellion. Balon's only surviving son [[Theon Greyjoy|Theon]] was made a ward of Lord [[Eddard Stark]] to ensure Balon's submission to King Robert.&lt;ref name=&quot;Balon Greyjoy viewers guide&quot;&gt;[http://viewers-guide.hbo.com/game-of-thrones/season2/#!/guide/houses/greyjoy/balon-greyjoy/ HBO viewers guide, season 2 guide to houses, House Greyjoy - Balon Greyjoy entry]&lt;/ref&gt; Only his daughter, [[Yara Greyjoy]], and two of his brothers remained on the Iron Islands after his defeat.&lt;ref name=&quot;Yara Greyjoy viewers guide&quot;&gt;[http://viewers-guide.hbo.com/game-of-thrones/season2/#!/guide/houses/greyjoy/yara-greyjoy/ HBO viewers guide, season 2 guide to houses, House Greyjoy - Yara Greyjoy entry]&lt;/ref&gt;
